<div id="c4">
<p>I agree that the TAL piece was excellent, but I wouldn&#8217;t say that the Guardian pieces conveys &#8216;far less&#8217; information.  Perhaps the Guardian didn&#8217;t touch on the relaxation of regulations for US mortgage applications prior to the &#8216;crunch&#8217;, but the general story and main issues (viz. nature of CDOs and rating agency mistakes) are still there.</p>

<p>Unfortunately many (most?) things are inherently complex and require more than a 2 minute segment in a news programme to allow viewers/readers to gain a thorough understanding.   My view is that the news media merely point out a subset of stories &#8212; usually relevant to only them and or their publishers/owners &#8212; and leave it to us to find out more.</p>

<p>I don&#8217;t think there is enough time in the day to allow one hour programmes examining each and every pressing issue arising in the world.</p>

